# DriftGuard (MCP / API contract drift)

When this repo has `mcp.json` or agent tool manifests, use **DriftGuard** for contract drift — offline first, hosted watches optional.

## MCP client config

Add the stdio server (copy [examples/mcp-client-config.json](https://github.com/Drift-Guard/driftguard/blob/main/examples/mcp-client-config.json)):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "driftguard": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "driftguard@0.3.3", "mcp"],
      "env": { "DRIFTGUARD_API_KEY": "" }
    }
  }
}
```

Omit `DRIFTGUARD_API_KEY` for fully offline use.

## Tool order (offline first)

1. `compare_json` — one-off before/after JSON schema diff (no key)
2. `parse_mcp_config` — preview URLs from mcp.json (no key)
3. `hosted_info` — free vs paid, trial, pricing (no key)
4. `explain_drift` — fix suggestions after breaking diff (no key)

Set `DRIFTGUARD_API_KEY` for continuous watches (`register_watch`, `assert_coverage`). Trial: https://driftguard.org/start

